======== Admin Security Suite Module v5.2.1.04 ========
Created by Joe Curia (azumandias _ at _ hotmail.com)
Original phorum coding by the Phorum Development Team (http://www.phorum.org)

========        Brief Description         ========
This security suite is designed to add additional security functions to a 
Phorum install.  Currently this module can monitor the forum title for hacks,
lockout IP addresses after a number of failed logins, restrict admin logins to
a set list of IP addresses, allow the admin to search for specific terms in all
of the settings saved in the admin area, add a captcha to the admin login, add 
monitoring of IP sessions to stop hackers from using a cookie to access the 
admin section without logging in, and restrict admin login to a schedule time 
period such as 9 AM to 5 AM.  Most security events will also be displayed in 
the Event Logging module.

========      Installation and Usage      ========
This module installs like any other module.  Help windows have been provided
for easy usage.  It is suggested that you enable the Event Loggin module and set 
it to display events on at least the warning level as a minimum.

